# Copy to `.env.production` (or set at build time) before building the native app.
# In web dev you can leave this unset — relative /api paths use the Vite proxy.
#
# For an App Store / native build, or ANY static-host deploy (Netlify, Vercel,
# etc.), point this at your DEPLOYED backend (HTTPS). Without this, the
# deployed frontend has no backend to talk to and every fetch will fail:
# VITE_API_BASE=https://api.weyn.app
VITE_API_BASE=

# Required in production. Used by the backend to build payment return URLs,
# payment webhook URLs, and team invite links. Do not take this from clients.
# PUBLIC_APP_URL=https://weyntickets.com
PUBLIC_APP_URL=

# Optional. Enables Google Places Autocomplete in the event-hosting map picker
# (much better real-address matching than the free OpenStreetMap fallback).
# Get a key at https://console.cloud.google.com/google/maps-apis — enable
# "Places API" and "Maps JavaScript API", then restrict the key to your
# domain(s) under "API restrictions" / "Application restrictions".
# Without this, the map picker still works via free OSM search — just less accurate.
VITE_GOOGLE_MAPS_KEY=

# Required for authentication. Clerk owns sign-in/session verification.
# VITE_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=
# CLERK_SECRET_KEY=

# Required for the external reminder cron endpoint.
# CRON_SECRET=

# Optional. Upgrades Instagram-caption parsing + marketing copy generation
# from deterministic templates to real Claude-generated text.
# Get one at https://console.anthropic.com
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# Optional. Apple Push Notifications — see HANDOFF.md section 7a for how to
# get these from your Apple Developer account.
# APN_KEY_ID=
# APN_TEAM_ID=
# APN_KEY=
# APN_BUNDLE_ID=com.weyn.app
# APN_PRODUCTION=false

# Required for the real Postgres database (replaces server/data.json).
# Get a free, no-expiry Postgres instance at https://neon.tech — sign up,
# create a project, and copy the connection string it gives you.
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:pass@ep-xxx.neon.tech/dbname?sslmode=require

# Payments for paid ("weyn" ticketing) tickets — two supported gateways,
# see server/payments.js for the provider-selection logic (Stripe wins if
# both are configured). Without either set, paid tickets can't be booked
# (event pages still work, free/RSVP events are unaffected).

# Option A: Stripe (stripe.com) — Checkout Sessions, hosted payment page.
# Get keys from https://dashboard.stripe.com/apikeys. VITE_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY
# is safe to expose client-side; STRIPE_SECRET_KEY is not. STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET
# comes from the webhook endpoint you create pointing at
# https://<your-domain>/api/payments/webhook for the checkout.session.*
# events (or via `stripe webhook_endpoints create` / the Stripe API directly).
# VITE_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=
# STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=
# STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=
# ⚠️ Weyn's prices are OMR — Stripe doesn't support OMR as a settlement
# currency, so server/payments-stripe.js currently charges in USD at a fixed
# illustrative conversion rate. Replace with a real FX rate or a supported
# settlement currency before accepting real (non-test-mode) payments.

# Option B: PayTabs (paytabs.com) — supports an individual/freelancer
# merchant tier with just a passport/national ID, no commercial registration
# needed. Get PAYTABS_PROFILE_ID from the dashboard's Profile > Info, and
# PAYTABS_SERVER_KEY from Profile > Key Management.
# PAYTABS_PROFILE_ID=
# PAYTABS_SERVER_KEY=
# PAYTABS_API_BASE=https://secure.paytabs.com
# ⚠️ PayTabs has region-specific domains (secure.paytabs.sa, .ae, .eg, etc) —
# confirm the exact one for your account in the dashboard before going live.

# Optional. Sends real team-invite emails via Resend (resend.com) instead of
# relying solely on the copy-link. Get a key at https://resend.com/api-keys.
# Without this set, invites still work — just copy-link only, no email sent.
# RESEND_API_KEY=
# RESEND_FROM=Weyn <noreply@weynevents.com>
